Management groups have several important characteristics:

* They support hierarchical organization
* Policies and RBAC roles are inherited
* Each directory can have a single root management group
* Subscriptions can belong to only one management group

For example, applying a policy at a parent management group automatically affects all child subscriptions.

A real-life use case is enterprise governance where security policies must be enforced across all departments.

Another example is compliance management in regulated industries, ensuring all resources meet specific standards.

Understanding these facts helps in designing scalable and secure Azure environments.
